(951, 'Since the 1960s the states have become[][]', 'more irrelevant to governance in modern society.[]', 'revitalized in their institutions, personnel and governance role.[]', 'less powerful in their policymaking capacity.[]', 'more homogeneous in how they govern. []', 2, 1, 'hard'),
(952, 'Every state is governed by ________, in which the basic rules of the political game for thatparticular state are established.[][]', 'the state government clause in the United States Constitution[]', 'a collection of state statutes[]', 'a state constitution[]', 'the laws of the United States Congress []', 3, 1, 'hard'),
(953, 'Most states[][]', 'do not have their own constitutions.[]', 'have constitutions more detailed and longer than the United States Constitution.[]', 'have unwritten constitutions rather than written constitutions.[]', 'have constitutions with about the same level of detail as the United States Constitution. []', 2, 1, 'hard'),
(954, 'Which of the following statements about state constitutions is FALSE?[][]', 'A state constitution spells out basic rules of the political game for that particular state.[]', 'State constitutions are subordinate to the United States Constitution.[]', 'State constitutions take precedence over state laws.[]', 'State constitutions are typically much shorter than the United States Constitution.[]', 4, 1, 'hard'),
