(961, 'Gubernatorial elections have become more   presidentialized   in that they[][]', 'have become more policy-oriented.[]', 'have come to rely on political party organizations more.[]', 'have become more personality-focused.[]', 'none of the above []', 3, 1, 'hard'),
(962, 'Since the 1960s, most states have[][]', 'shifted gubernatorial elections to off-Presidential years.[]', 'reduced the number of elected state executives.[]', 'changed the governor\'s term of office to four years.[]', 'both A and C[]', 4, 1, 'hard'),
