(970, 'Divided government exists when[][]', 'the major parties do not control both chambers of the state legislature and a majority of state elected officials.[]', 'a single party does not control both chambers of the state legislature and a majority of state elected offices.[]', 'a single party does not control both chambers of the state legislature and the governor\'s office.[]', 'when the Republicans and the Democrats hold an equal number of congressional seats. []', 1, 2, 'hard'),
