(973, 'The ten-year turnover of state legislative seats[][]', 'occurs at a very slow rate.[]', 'averages over 90 percent.[]', 'results in a significant change in the people holding office.[]', 'results in a completely new legislature every ten years. []', 3, 3, 'hard'),
(974, 'Which of these is INCORRECT?[][]', 'The Nebraska legislature only has one house.[]', 'Although it is the second largest state, the Texas legislature is only scheduled to meet every other year.[]', 'All states now limit the terms of their legislators.[]', 'Many state legislators are part-timers who have other careers. []', 3, 1, 'hard'),
