(982, 'The fact that most states have a number of elected state executives in addition to the governor[][]', 'gives the governor greater authority.[]', 'reduces the authority of the governor.[]', 'reduces the democratic accountability of the executive branch of state government.[]', 'has no effect on the authority of the governor. []', 2, 2, 'hard'),
(983, 'A governor\'s control over policy administration is somewhat diminished because[][]', 'new state constitutions tend to limit the powers of the governor.[]', 'a large number of other executive branch officials are also elected in most states.[]', 'state legislatures have taken over many traditional executive duties.[]', 'all of the above []', 2, 2, 'hard'),
(984, 'The governor and lieutenant governor are elected in separate elections and can be of differentparties[][]', 'in all fifty states.[]', 'in about half the states.[]', 'in eight states.[]', 'in about one-third of the states. []', 2, 3, 'hard'),
(985, 'The lieutenant governor[][]', 'is appointed by the governor in 43 states.[]', 'runs separately from the governor in seven states.[]', 'does not exist in seven states.[]', 'runs with the governor as a team in eight states. []', 3, 2, 'hard'),
