(995, 'A recent policy change in some states that actually   deprofessionalizes   legislature is[][]', 'sunset legislation.[]', 'line-item veto.[]', 'term limits.[]', 'Missouri Plan. []', 3, 3, 'hard'),
(996, 'The judicial system in most states is set up[][]', 'as the lowest level of the federal court system, with the states having little say over structure or operations.[]', 'in a haphazard fashion, with trial courts and appellate courts differing county by county, municipality by municipality.[]', 'without an appellate level; any appeals of state trial court decisions go directly to the United States Supreme Court.[]', 'as a hierarchical system under state control, similar in its organization to the federal court system.[]', 4, 1, 'hard'),
