(335, 'The   responsible party   model holds that parties should[][]', 'not use wedge issues that cause the other party\'s supporters to fight with each other during the campaign.[]', 'avoid making promises.[]', 'keep to middle-of-the-road positions.[]', 'present clear alternatives to voters.[]', 4, 2, 'medium'),
(336, 'In what way do weak political parties affect the scope of government?[][]', 'They make it difficult for politicians to help their constituents.[]', 'They allow presidents to expand the scope of foreign policy, while they decrease the domestic scope of government.[]', 'Being weak, they are unable to counteract the power of government so the scope of government grows.[]', 'Since it is harder for them to enact legislation, it is hard for them to either expand or decrease the scope of government.[]', 4, 1, 'medium'),
